  "description": "ASAP6b (also called ASAP6.2) is an improved positively tuned ASAP variant engineered for higher molecular brightness at physiological resting potentials. Its fluorescence-voltage input range is shifted to more negative voltages compared to ASAP6.1, so it operates at higher baseline brightness near -70 mV. It exhibits a mono-exponential activation time constant of 3.7 ms and produces a 33% ΔF/F per action potential in HEK293 cells, outperforming ASAP4e (23%). ASAP6b reliably reports action potentials in cultured neurons, retinal ganglion cells, and cortical layer 2/3 neurons in vivo using both one-photon and two-photon microscopy.",
